attachments.title: automate cleaning up bad decks

attachments.fallback: David Keatts updated the description of automate cleaning up bad decks.
attachments.text:
currently there's an issue where - scryfall will sometimes have wrong names for translated cards during spoiler season.  decks end up with our database with those names, then the names update but those decks sit around forever.

I wouldn't want to automatically delete these decks (sounds dangerous) but it would be nice to have a shell script that prints out # of decks with each bad card and prompts to delete them (or something)
attachments.pretext: Updated the description of *<https://trello.com/c/kCLFb9rB|automate cleaning up bad decks>*.
